---
description: Require unit tests for new backend and frontend functionality
alwaysApply: true
---

# Testing required

- New backend functionality must include pytest unit tests with at least one positive and one negative case.
- New frontend functionality must include Vitest tests for logic, hooks, or components touched by the change.
- Extract pure functions from pages when needed to keep UI tests focused on behavior.
- Before considering feature work complete, run:
  - `cd backend && pytest`
  - `cd frontend && npm test`
- Do not merge feature work without adding or updating tests in the same change.
